[00:04.750]No two sorts of birds practice quite the same sort of flight. | 没有哪两种鸟的飞行方式是完全相同的。
[00:09.110]The varieties are infinite, but two classes may be roughly seen. | 种类繁多，但大致可分为两类。
[00:14.370]Any ship that crosses the Pacific is accompanied for many days by the smaller albatross, | 任何横渡太平洋的船只，都会有多日受到较小的信天翁的陪伴，
[00:19.670]which may keep company with the vessel for an hour without visible or more than occasional movement of wing. | 它可以陪伴船只一个小时，而翅膀没有明显的，或只是偶尔的摆动。
[00:27.200]The currents of air that the walls of the ship direct upwards, | 船壁向上引导的气流，
[00:30.820]as well as in the line of its course, | 以及沿着船只航线的气流，
[00:33.000]are enough to give the great bird with its immense wings sufficient sustenance and progress. | 足以让这只拥有巨大翅膀的大鸟获得足够的支撑和前进动力。
[00:39.460]The albatross is the king of the gliders, | 信天翁是滑翔鸟之王，
[00:42.270]the class of flyers which harness the air to their purpose, but must yield to its opposition. | 它们是利用空气达到目的的飞行者，但必须顺从空气的阻力。
[00:48.740]In the contrary school, the duck is supreme. | 在相反的学派中，鸭子是至高无上的。
[00:51.680]It comes nearer to the engines with which man has conquered the air, as he boasts. | 它更接近于人类征服空气所使用的引擎，正如人类所夸耀的那样。
[00:56.590]Duck, unlike them the pigeons, are endowed with steel-like muscles that are a good part of the weight of the bird. | 鸭子，与鸽子不同，被赋予了钢铁般的肌肉，占了鸟体重量的很大一部分。
[01:04.380]And these will ply the short wings with irresistible power that can bear them for long distances through an opposite gale before exhaustion follows. | 它们会以不可抗拒的力量扇动短小的翅膀，即使在逆风中也能长距离飞行，直到筋疲力尽。
[01:14.400]Their humbler followers, such as partridges, have a like power of strong propulsion, but soon tire. | 它们更卑微的追随者，如鹧鸪，也有类似的强大推进力，但很快就会疲劳。
[01:21.870]You may pick them up in utter exhaustion if wind over the sea has driven them to a long journey. | 如果海风驱使它们进行长途旅行，你可能会发现它们筋疲力尽地倒下。
[01:28.930]The swallow shares the virtues of both schools in highest measure. | 燕子兼具两派的优点，表现出色。
[01:33.320]It tires not, nor does it boast of its power, | 它不知疲倦，也不炫耀自己的力量，
